    <Paragraph FontSize="20">Entity</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>
        <Run FontStyle="Italic">Many objects represent a thread of continuity and identity, going through a lifecycle, though their attributes may change.</Run>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph LineHeight="10">
        <Run>Some objects are not defined primarily by their attributes. They represent a thread of identity that runs through time and often across distinct representations. Sometimes such an object must be matched with another object even though attributes differ. An object must be distinguished from other objects even though they might have the same attributes. Mistaken identity can lead to data corruption.</Run>
    </Paragraph>
